I would want to work with you more if you were able to meet your commitments. If you are unable to meet commitments, please communicate that quickly and directly and not leave things open-ended. This week was challenging for various reasons, and I gave you zero contribution because you weren't physically here the majority of the time. Please know that this was a very tough decision to give you zero. Once you started with the back-end, it broke our ability to show off the front-end that was already completed and since the cog app on Friday wasn't there, we didn't learn anything to be able to learn it and fix it ourselves. Self-care is imperative so that illnesses and outside stressors aren't detrimental to your project. I was honest on Friday when I said that I was uncomfortable with the position you were in with your founder. The agenda that was also presented on Friday regarding space issues and the tables had me feeling very frustrated and cornered.

value:
Your overall technical skills are great.  You have a really good knowledge of the project and how everything goes together.  I appreciate your dedication to getting that Selenium stuff done.  I also found you to be very kind and accepting.

I know it was largely due to the tasks we were working on and the environment where we were working, (and myself being in a withdrawn mood much of the week) but I wish we'd had more of a chance to work together.  I know, for myself, I have a harder time focusing when I'm not working with someone. 

We also fell into the pattern of the person who knows a task best is always the one driving, and I normally prefer the reverse (Not that that is necessarily your problem.  Just kind of an observation about the week).
 I think you could work on your ability to explain things and give directions, though perhaps we just didn't get to work in the circumstances where that would have come up.

Also, I would have appreciated better communication in the mornings when you are running late.  There were a couple days where we hadn't heard anything from you before 9.

value: I appreciated that you were very present and punctual the entire time we worked together, thats something that I definitely feel like I need to work on. I would encourage you to be a little bit more vocal and communicative in how you're feeling in the project because I felt you were a little bit overwhelmed with React and I didn't full understand if you wanted or needed more help and how I could be of better help. I tend to be someone who goes full steam ahead if the code is making sense to me but I really appreciate questions on how I am doing things, or just questions about how the code that we are writing is operating. Having someone ask me questions allows me to reflect on the work we have put it and also let me know how you are feeling or if its making sense. I felt we could have had more feedback flowing and I would encourage you to check in a little bit more often next time we work together and I will do the same. All in all, I had a good time working with you and hope you did too and are feeling well again!

I also liked how well you received feedback, and noticed in yourself when you were dravigating, and did not attempt to "hide" by switching subjects. value:

I don't have a lot of feedback for you cause you have the right attitude to be a software developer and your communication skills are very good. My only technical feedback is to practice styling as you write your code and the best way to do it is to always ask yourself can someone else read my code and fully understand it? if you keep that question with you along the way you write your code you'll be unstoppable. 
Best of luck to you bro, you'll do great!!
